First Call for Papers
International Workshop on Evolution and Change in Data Management , ECDM'99 15 - 18 November 1999
to be held in conjunction with the
18 th International Conference on Conceptual Modelling , ER'99 Versailles , France , November 15 - 18 , 1999
The management of evolution and change and the ability for data , information and knowledge-based systems to deal with change is an essential component in developing truly useful systems . Many approaches to handling evolution and change have been proposed in various areas of data management and this forum seeks to bring together researchers from both more established areas and those from emerging areas to look at this issue . This workshop will deal with the manner in which change can be handled , and the semantics of evolving data and data structure in computer based systems . Topics include , but are not limited to :
* Change Detection in Computer-based Systems * Change Maintenance in Internet-based Data ! ! bases * Handling Change in Temporal Databases * Induction of Cause and Effect * Modelling Evolution and Change * Schema Evolution / Schema Versioning * Semantics of Time and Change * Summary Database Maintenance * Temporal Data Mining * View Maintenance in Databases
Publication of Proceedings
The workshop proceedings will be published as part of the Springer , Lecture Notes in Computer Science series under the title Advances in Database Technology , Vol 2 .
Format and submission of papers
Format of submissions will as for the main International Conference on Conceptual Modelling and the other workshops ( 12 pages in Springer 's , Lecture Notes in Computer Science standard format ) . Submissions should be by electronic mail to ecdm 99 @ cs . unisa . edu . au in postscript format by the due date . All correspondence with authors will be via e-mail so please ensure that your submission includes an e-mail address for the corresponding author . Paper format can be found at the workshop website ! ! http : / / www . cis . unisa . edu . au / events / ecdm 99 .
Panel Proposals
Proposals for panel sessions , which should be approximately one page outlining the intent , format and outcomes of the panel , should be sent to the programme chair , by the due date . Notification will be given on the same date as notification of paper acceptances . Important Dates
* Papers Due April 30 , 1999 * Panel Proposals due April 30 , 1999 * Notification of Acceptances June 30 , 1999 * Camera Ready Copy August 10 , 1999 * Workshop Dates November 15 - 18 , 1999

About ER'99
The International Conference on Conceptual Modeling provides an international forum for presenting and discussing current research and applications in which the major emphasis is on conceptual modeling . The conference was originally devoted to the Entity- Relationship ( ER ) model , but has long since expanded to include all types of semantic data modeling , behavior and process modeling , and object-oriented systems modeling . The conference embraces all phases of software development including analysis , specification , design , implementation , evolution and reengineering . It is the aim of this conference to present state-of-the-art research on emerging topics in conceptual modeling , to review important techniques in related areas , and to discuss ap ! ! plication papers of interest to information system professionals as well as information technology academics and researchers .
Further details can be found at the ER'99 website http : / / www . prism . uvsq . fr / er 99 .
Location
This will be one of three workshops held in conjunction with the 18 th International Conference on Conceptual Modelling , ER'99 , in Versailles , France .
